    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Boil a kettle and heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a high heat</p><p>Chop your <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halved cherry tomatoes</strong> to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 2 min</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>fresh</strong> <strong>orecchiette</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled</strong> <strong>water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook the <strong>orecchiette </strong>for 4-6 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>orecchiette</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy</strong> <strong>pasta</strong> <strong>water</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and slice (don't chop!) your<strong> garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>in 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[130ml</span>] <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced garlic</strong> and your <strong>'Nduja</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan with the tomatoes and cook for 3-4 min, breaking up the 'Nduja with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Tear <strong>half</strong> your <strong>basil leaves </strong>(save the rest for garnish!) into the pan along with the <strong>chicken stock </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>'Nduja & cherry tomato sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained orecchiette </strong>to the pan and give everything a gentle mix up until the pasta is coated in the sauce \u2013 this is your<strong> 'Nduja & cherry tomato sauce with fresh orecchiette</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/nduja-and-cherry-tomato-sauce-with-fresh-orecchiette/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>'Nduja & cherry tomato sauce with fresh orecchiette </strong>topped with your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>and tear over the <strong>remaining basil leaves</strong></p><p>Drizzle with a little <strong>olive oil </strong>and season with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
